CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 16, 1950, pg. 2, reads: "Pitt Summer Commencement - Numerous Negro students were among the persons graduating or receiving degrees at the University of Pittsburgh's summer commencement held in Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall last Friday evening. Among them were top left: Raymond E. Dorsey, Jesse B. Adams and James H. Blair, all graduates of the college.  Pictured with them is James G. French, who received his degree in electrical engineering.... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of University of Pittsburgh graduates Raymond E. Dorsey, Jesse B. Adams, James H. Blair, and James G. French, posed in hallway of Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall
